## Wzorzec

Rysujaca sie pozioma linia z centrum na obie strony, z glow i jednorazowym glitch bursten. Uzywa `useScrollProgress` zamiast `whileInView` — pelna synchronizacja ze scroll progress PinSection.

Roznica vs [[Framer Motion whileInView scaleX DrawLine — horizontal line draw]]: tamten rysuje od lewej, jest prostszy, nie ma glow/glitch. Ten rysuje symetrycznie z centrum, wymaga scroll context.

## Kod

```tsx
import { motion, useAnimationControls, useMotionValueEvent } from "motion/react";
import { useRef } from "react";
import { useScrollProgress, useScrollTransform } from "@/hooks/useScrollProgress";

function DrawLine() {
  const scrollYProgress = useScrollProgress();

  // Two halves scale from center (0 → 1) over first 15% of scroll
  const halfScale = useScrollTransform([0, 0.15], [0, 1]);

  // Glow fades in as line finishes drawing
  const glow = useScrollTransform<string>(
    [0.10, 0.18],
    [
      "0 0 0px rgba(251,73,0,0)",
      "0 0 10px 3px rgba(251,73,0,0.55), 0 0 28px 8px rgba(251,73,0,0.22)",
    ],
  );

  // One-shot glitch burst when line finishes
  const leftCtrl = useAnimationControls();
  const rightCtrl = useAnimationControls();
  const glitched = useRef(false); // useRef, NOT let — let resets every render

  useMotionValueEvent(scrollYProgress, "change", (v) => {
    if (v >= 0.14 && !glitched.current) {
      glitched.current = true;
      const glitchAnim = {
        x: [0, 3, -3, 2, -2, 1, 0],
        opacity: [1, 0.3, 1, 0, 1, 0.6, 1],
        transition: { duration: 0.45, ease: "linear" as const },
      };
      leftCtrl.start(glitchAnim);
      rightCtrl.start(glitchAnim);
    }
  });

  const halfStyle = {
    position: "absolute" as const,
    top: 0,
    height: "100%",
    width: "50%",
  };

  return (
    <div
      role="presentation"
      aria-hidden="true"
      style={{ position: "relative", width: "100%", height: "1px", flexShrink: 0 }}
    >
      {/* Left half — origin: right (grows center → left) */}
      <motion.div
        animate={leftCtrl}
        style={{
          ...halfStyle,
          right: "50%",
          transformOrigin: "right",
          scaleX: halfScale,
          boxShadow: glow,
          background:
            "linear-gradient(to left, rgba(251,73,0,0.40) 0%, rgba(251,73,0,0.40) 80%, transparent 100%)",
        }}
      />
      {/* Right half — origin: left (grows center → right) */}
      <motion.div
        animate={rightCtrl}
        style={{
          ...halfStyle,
          left: "50%",
          transformOrigin: "left",
          scaleX: halfScale,
          boxShadow: glow,
          background:
            "linear-gradient(to right, rgba(251,73,0,0.40) 0%, rgba(251,73,0,0.40) 80%, transparent 100%)",
        }}
      />
    </div>
  );
}
```

